SUMMARY:Steep & Paint: Magnolia
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy a blossom-filled afternoon at the beautiful Lan Su Chinese Garden with the return of Steep & Paint! \n\n\n\nBack by popular demand and newly reimagined in partnership with the Oregon Botanical Artists (OBA). This immersive afternoon experience invites you to slow down\, look closely\, and connect with plants through tea\, conversation\, and hands-on artmaking. \n\n\n\nEach session weaves together horticulture\, tea culture\, and botanical art in a relaxed\, welcoming setting: \n\n\n\nLearn the plant up close: A Lan Su gardener leads a close-up botanical show-and-tell\, sharing seasonal plant facts\, cultural stories\, and growing insights. \n\n\n\nTaste the season: Enjoy a sampling of seasonal teas from Yun Shui Teahouse. \n\n\n\nCreate botanical art: An OBA artist guides a full botanical art class inspired by the featured plant. \n\n\n\nWhether you’re returning to Steep & Paint or joining for the first time\, this refreshed program offers an even richer way to experience Lan Su. Bring a friend with you and let’s Steep & Paint together! \n\n\n\nFull Series Schedule\n\n\n\n2-5PM\, April 10 & 24 – Magnolia2-5PM\, May 15 & 22 – Peony2-5PM\, June 12 & 26 – Penjing2-5PM\, July 17 & 31 & Aug 14– Lotus2-5PM\, August 28 – Bamboo2-5PM\, September 11 & 25 – Osmanthus1-4PM\, October 16 & 30 – Begonia1-4PM\, November 13 & 20 – Chrysanthemum1-4PM\, December 4 & 18 – Camellia1-4PM\, January 8 & 22 – Plum Blossom\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSteep & Paint Need to Know \n\n\n\nEach class session is independent — participants are welcome to register for any individual class without attending others. \n\n\n\nRegistration fee includes full-day admission to Lan Su Chinese Garden. \n\n\n\nGet Tickets\n\n\n\n\nLan Su Members: $56.95\n\n\n\nGeneral: $66.95\n\n\n\n\nNote: A $0.95 service fee is reflected in each paid ticket \n\n\n\n\nGet Tickets\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nOregon Botanical Artists (OBA)  \n\n\n\nOregon Botanical Artists is a nonprofit organization dedicated to promoting contemporary botanical art while honoring its long-standing traditions. Founded in 2012\, the organization supports a diverse community of artists who celebrate the beauty and diversity of plant life through detailed and scientifically informed artwork. Oregon Botanical Artists is affiliated with the American Society of Botanical Artists as an Artists Circle. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nParking & Directions\n\n\n\nFree Lan Su Parking\n\n\n\nThere is free first come\, first served parking in our sister lot next to the garden at 424 NW Third Avenue. Additional metered parking and garages are available on surrounding streets.
URL:https://lansugarden.org/event/steep-paint-magnolia-april-10/
LOCATION:Lan Su Chinese Garden\, 239 NW Everett Street\, Portland\, Oregon\, 97209
CATEGORIES:Art,Magnolia Festival,Tea
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://lansugarden.org/wp-content/uploads/steep-and-paint-2026.webp
END:VEVENT
